Directives.
    - Directives in AngularJS Enhances the HTML Capabilities.

    - We Have Two Types Of Directives.

        1. Predefined Directives.

        2. Custom Directives.

Predefined Directives.
    - The Directives Given By the Framework Called as Predefined Directives.

1.ng-app

    - it is a root directive in angular application.

    - framework starts the execution from ng-app directive.

    - ng-app directive takes the "logical name" of web application.

    - "logical name of application" optional for static angular applications.

    - "logical name of applications" are mandatory for dynamic angular applications.

    - we can take only one "ng-app" directive per web application.

    - Executing the Angular Application Forcefully without ng-app called as Manual Bootstrap.




Custom Directives.


    - In AngularJS we Can Use Custom Directives in 3 ways.

    1. Element

    2. CSS Class

    3. Attribute


    Ex.

        my_directive.


        <my_directive></my_directive> //Element

        <div class="my_directive"></div> //CSS Class

        <div my_directive></div>   //Attribute

Properties Of Custom Directive.
-

1. restrict

    - it will describe usage of custom directive.

Ex.

    restrict : "E" //Element Level Usage

    restrict : "A" // Attribute Level Usage

    restrict : "C" // CSS Class Level Usage

    restrict : "EC" // Element & CSS Class

------------------
app.directive("attrType",attrType);

function attrType(){

    return{
        restrict:"A"
    }
}


<div attr-type></div>


2. template

    - used to add the inline HTML to the Custom Directive.

Ex.

    app.directive("classType",classType);

    function classType(){

        return{
            restrict:"C",
            template : "<div>Welcome to Custom Directives !</div>"
        }
    }


    <div class="class-type"></div> //Welcome to Custom Directives !


3. templateUrl.

       - used to add the external template to the Custom Directive.
Ex.
--------
templates
       sample.html
--------
sample.html
-
<h1>Welcome to Custom Directives !</h1>

app.directive("elemType",elemType);
function elemType(){
       return{
            restrict:"E",
            templateUrl:"templates/sample.html"
       }
}
<elem-type></elem-type> //Welcome to Custom Directives !

4.controller
       - used to define the controller to the template of a custom directive.
Ex.
-------
templates
       sample.html
-------
<h1>{{var_one}}</h1>

-------
controller
       sample.js
--------
sample.js
-
app.controller("sample",sample);
sample.$inject=["$scope"];
function sample($scope){
    $scope.var_one="I am from Custom Directive !";
}
--------
directives
    allType.js
---------
app.directive("allType",allType);
function allType(){
    return{
        restrict:"EAC",
        templateUrl:"templates/sample.html",
        controller:"sample"
    }
}
<all-type></all-type> //Element
<div class="all-type"></div> //CSS Class
<div all-type></div> //Attribute Type Usage

                *************************************
Example_1
    bower.json
    .bowerrc
    app.js
    index.html
    directives(folder)
         attrType.js
         classType.js
         elemType.js
         allType.js
                ******************************************

bower.json
-
{
    "name":"nareshit",
    "dependencies":{
        "angular":"~1.6.0",
        "bootstrap":"~3.3.6"
    }
}

.bowerrc
{
    "directory":"bower_components"
}

app.js
-
var app = angular.module("app",[]);

index.html
-
<html ng-app="app">
    <!-- attrType-->
    <div class="container" attr-type></div>
    <!-- elemType -->
    <div class="container">
        <elem-type></elem-type>
    </div>
    <!-- classType -->
    <div class="container class-type"></div>
    <!-- allType-->
    <div class="container all-type"></div>
    <div class="container" all-type></div>
    <div class="container">
        <all-type></all-type>
    </div>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <script src="bower_component/angular/angular.min.js"></script>
    <script src="app.js"></script>
    <script src="directives/attrType.js"></script>
    <script src="directives/classType.js"></script>
    <script src="directives/elemType.js"></script>
    <script src="directives/allType.js"></script>
</html>











